Marcell sees his younger brother Jordan‚Äôs aptitude in math and science, so when he imagines him in high school, he feels reassured by Coney Island Prep‚Äôs expansion.
‚ÄúHaving a bigger campus with more students means my little brother won‚Äôt need to go elsewhere to get a comprehensive high school experience,‚Äù he says.

With a full-sized gym and ample science labs, Marcell knows that Jordan‚Äôs passions will be nurtured at Coney Island Prep.

With the possibility of snow tonight and tomorrow, we want to remind you of our inclement weather policy.

CIP follows the decisions of the NYC Department of Education (DOE) as it relates to school closures due to inclement weather.
- If the DOE is closed, Coney Island Prep is closed.
- If the DOE is open, Coney Island Prep is open.
- If the DOE is delayed, Coney Island Prep is delayed.

If you would like to check, a great place to find out this information is the DOE Twitter page linked here: https://twitter.com/NYCSchools?ref_src=twsrc%5Egoogle%7Ctwcamp%5Eserp%7Ctwgr%5Eauthor

Congratulations to Sydney Gately, from our first class of graduates, on her acceptance to the selective group of 2018 Morgan Stanley Summer Teaching Fellows with The Partnership for After School Education (PASE)!

Sydney joins a group of 20 other students from colleges around the country to enhance the educational opportunities and learning experiences for children living in poverty so they return to school ready to learn.

Sydney's goal is to come back and teach at Coney Island Prep, and we can't wait!

post_text:
Happy Veterans Day! A special thank you to all those who served our country, and now serve our scholars.

People like Kevin Torres, who is from South Brooklyn, served two tours in Iraq as an infantryman in the 101st Airborne Division of the U.S. Army, and then came back to Brooklyn to be a teacher. Kevin is now Coney Island Prep Middle School's 8th Grade Vice Principal.

For more of Kevin's story, click here: http://coneyislandprep.org/elementary-school/serving-country-serving-scholars/
